25|$|Although the cubical {{model of}} the atom was soon {{abandoned}} {{in favor of the}} quantum mechanical model based on the SchrÃ¶dinger equation, and is therefore now principally of historical interest, it represented an important step towards the understanding of the <b>chemical</b> <b>bond.</b> The 1916 article by Lewis also introduced the concept of the electron pair in the covalent bond, the octet rule, and the now-called Lewis structure.|$|E
